Description: Fragment of sub-round handle from neck join to sharp turn of a Rhodianpottery transport amphora. Clay fine beige. Rectangular stamp with winged caduceus symbol.
Curator's comments: Possible ink traces. Name Philokrates. There are examples in the same messy condition, from the same die, in the Benaki collection, Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, e.g. MGR P.15884.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (217)
